===Noun Suffix===
'''-ric''', plural '''-rics'''

# kingdom; domain; realm.  Noun suffix once appended to various words, but surviving only in:
#: ''[[bishopric]]''
#: ''[[archbishopric]]''

====Etymology====
From Germanic and [[Proto-Indo-European]]; akin to German '''[[Reich]]''', ''kingdom'', Latin '''[[regnum]]''', ''kingdom'', '''[[rex]]''', ''king'', '''[[regere]]''', ''rule'', and many other words.

